title.narrative: “One stop shop” project development platform supported under umbrella of SAEE with Ukrainian-Danish expertise.
Support provided to State Agency for Energy Efficiency (SAEE) including on energy efficiency and renewable energy projects, development of technical feasibility studies and new finance models.
Tools for integration of renewable energy, short-term forecast of production, development of wind measuring infrastructure and Ukraine’s efforts to converge its electricity market regulation to EU.

Tools and methodologies proposed to support integration of renewables in Ukrainian electricity system including need for flexible thermal generation, storage capacity, renewable energy auction design to facilitate integration of renewable energy.
Final progres report, final financial report and final results report received from implementing agent: Danish Energy Agency.
Ukraine supported in increasing share of renewable energy in total energy consumption by 2020 and reducing climate and environmental impact of fossil fuel based energy sector.
Level of integration and implementation of renewable energy and energy efficiency projects.
